  "texts": [
    "In this part of our study, we employ keyword and co-occurrence analyses to explore the latest research trends and advancements in using artificial intelligence for the diagnosis, prognosis and treatment of breast cancer.",
    "Our objective is to pinpoint research gaps and predict future directions in this domain. \"",
    "The primary keywords are illustrated in Fig. 4, with \"mammography\" (3171 occurrences) being the most frequent, followed by \"female\" (1739), \"artificial intelligence\" (1691), \"human\" (1483), and \"breast cancer\" (1444).",
    "Additionally, the relationship between AI and breast cancer diagnosis, prognosis and treatment research is depicted using the word growth graph in Fig. 5 and Table 8.",
    "This graph shows a progressive increase in the annual occurrence of key terms related to AI tools for early breast cancer diagnosis, such as \"breast cancer,\" \"deep learning (DL),\"\" \"machine learning (ML),\" \"feature selection,\" and \"classification.\""
  ],
